# transactionIdentifier

**Instance Property**

A unique transaction identifier that the system generates.

## Declaration

```swift
var transactionIdentifier: String { get }
```

## Discussion

The system generates this value when you call [doc://com.apple.storekittest/documentation/StoreKitTest/SKAdTestSession/setPostbacks(_:)]. This value is an empty string otherwise.

Use this value to match the test postback with the response you receive from [doc://com.apple.storekittest/documentation/StoreKitTest/SKAdTestSession/flushPostbacks(responses:)].

## Getting general information

- **version**: The SKAdNetwork version that the postback uses.
- **postbackSequenceIndex**: The position of this postback among all postbacks for an ad impression.
- **isRegistered**: A Boolean value that indicates whether the postback is registered in the testing environment.
- **isRedownload**: A Boolean value that indicates whether the user redownloaded and reinstalled the app.
